Exclusive: 3 or 6-course destination dining experience
description:
Check availability for your private group and experience Destination Dining in the Puget Sound. The Pretty Fork is defining the dining experience through exclusive and communal dinner reservations in Seattle and the Pacific Northwest. Founders Joey Manley and Michael Watts work with the premier restaurants and chefs in the region to create custom menus tailored to each guest for a truly carefree dining experience. We ask that you give us at least 3 weeks to plan your adventure, planes are very limited.

Have a group bigger than 4 people? Want an overnight food-focused glamping experience? What about something more local?

name: Exclusive: 6 or 9-course tasting menu tours
description:
Arranging a networking event? Traveling with a group from out of town? Are you a local Seattleite? Check availability for your private group of 6 or more. The Pretty Fork is defining the dining experience through exclusive and communal reservations in Seattle and the Pacific Northwest. Founders Joey Manley and Michael Watts work with the premier restaurants and chefs in the region to create custom menus tailored to each guest for a truly carefree dining experience. 

Have a group bigger than 6 people? Check out our other availability on Tock.

Want something more refined? Request information and reserve a seaplane for a Destination Dining experience: a six-course farm-to-fork experience in the San Juan Islands.

name: Seattle Brewery Tour
description: Enjoy the visit to three distinct Seattle breweries in three hours on a beer and brewery tour, and get to take home a cool t-shirt and souvenir pint glass to boot. You'll be provided with safe transport along the way and the opportunity to make new, like-minded friends. Inside the breweries, you'll become acquainted with the facts and figures of what goes into a beautiful brew. Information on the history, culture and technical aspects of a good brew will be freely dispensed and of course, so will the beer! Lots of tastings are included with this tour to drink and enjoy. Learning has never been more delicious.

review.name: Brilliant fun for 8 straight years
review.reviewBody: Six of us go on this tour every year around the Holidays - we love it.  Drivers/tour-guides/beer-experts are amazing.  We have such fun each year and can't wait to come back each year!

review.name: Great time but pricey
review.reviewBody:
Ben was an outstanding tour guide! A lot of knowledge, a great sense of humor, and a wonderful personality. He provided us with information about the city, beer, and introduced us to many breweries we would have never explored having not taken the tour. Ben made the trip for us!
Although, the price was a bit too much especially when you need to provide a tip.

review.name: Wow- Really sexist drivers
review.reviewBody: Our guide was knowledgeable, but kept making racist jokes and sexist remarks. I called the owner Dustin to complain and was met with a similar attitude, not what I was expecting from a seattle company.  Very rude.

review.name: Best (and Worst)
review.reviewBody: My friend and I toured with the Road Dogs Brewery Tour.  Since we booked the early spot, it was just me and her and the tour guide. It became one of the best (and worst) beer tour I ever had.  The best is because since we're a small group, we get to check out breweries where most tour groups can't go (due to size). The worst (for me) is they are a LOT of samples which I roughly estimate to be about 25-30 drinks ( I can't remember). By the third stop, I was really buzzed and about to pass out in the middle of the day. Luckily, my friend was there to prop me up.  I highly recommend the early spots so you can actually see what you're drinking.

review.name: Excellent Brewery Tour!
review.reviewBody: We had such a blast on our Seattle Brewery tour! Our guide David was extremely knowledgeable and friendly, he was a fantastic tour guide! This is a perfect tour for beer lovers, we loved that we got to pick our flights and got great recommendations on what beers we should try. So glad we took that tour, met some really cool beer lovers and had a great time!

review.name: Great Experience
review.reviewBody:
Our tour guide Adam was great -- very knowledgeable, funny, made the tour great. I know some reviews mentioned driver drinking, but Adam didn't and I'm very happy about that as that was something I was worried about before we got there.
My small group (me, boyfriend, his 2 siblings) had a good time, and they had alot of great beer (I was D.D. so no drinking for me). 
Adam picked great breweries and great beers for my group to try.
The whole drive home my group was talking about how great the tour was, how great Adam was, how we gotta do this again, etc.
The shirt and pint glass you get as part of your tour appear to be good quality as well.
Great experience!

review.name: Fun and Informative Beer Tour!
review.reviewBody: We hit three breweries on the tour (varies each time)- Pyramid, Hale's and Bad Jimmies... we had a small group (just 3 of us) so we had a great one-on-one tour experience. Tour guide was funny, informative and friendly-- you could tell he enjoyed his job. Def would recommend this tour! Hit the Seattle Beer Company for a flight upon our return.... no driving and we were just tipsy enough to enjoy the rest of our afternoon! Beer lovers will enjoy!

review.name: Fun day
review.reviewBody: My family of four enjoyed the tour. We had it all to ourselves. Dave ( Our tour guide) was knowledgeable and fun and did a great job of going the extra mile for our needs and wants. At first I thought it was a bit spendy, but overall I think it was a good value. We got a t-shirt, a beer mug, a ride, plenty of yummy tasting beers and got to visit some new places in Seattle. We had a wonderful afternoon.

review.name: Fun and informative
review.reviewBody:
Great tour, informative and interesting. Our guide, Adam, was very knowledgeable and engaging.

We toured three very different breweries in three different areas of Seattle. Each was off the beaten path, so I would not have come across them on my own in typical tourist activities. We had beer flights at each stop, with Adam providing info and answering questions. 

The guide was an excellent driver and did not drink any alcohol during the tour.

Good value, fun way to see Seattle outside of the tourist zones.

review.name: Probably the best brew tour I've been on
review.reviewBody:
First things first, this tour is not a behind the scenes tour of a brewery. Instead, the intent of the tour is to introduce you to the myriad of styles of beers brewed by the many breweries in Seattle. I actually preferred this because too often the 'behind the scenes' tour is just a sanitized tourist version of what actually happens on the brewery floor. Instead I was treated to really good beer and really good discussion about what makes each beer different. This style of tour lends itself to novice and experienced beer drinkers alike because there is enough variety to satisfy everyone's expectations while still offering something different for those that want that experience. 

I wish I could remember my tour guide's name because he was excellent (Thursday, 14 June 1430 tour). I will most definitely take this tour again.

name: Seattle Dinner Cruise
description: Enjoy an unforgettable dining experience aboard a beautiful Waterways yacht - complete with a delicious four-course dinner, friendly, attentive service, and stunning views of Seattle's lakes and city skylines.

review.name: Seattle, the Beautiful!
review.reviewBody: We booked a Holiday Dinner Cruise to celebrate three birthdays.  The crew were outstanding, very professional, friendly, and helpful.  The food was cooked to perfection.  The  December weather was perfect, and the view from the deck is a wonderful way to see the beautiful Seattle skyline, all lit up.  It was a memorable cruise for all the guests and we are planning our next cruise.

review.name: Wonderful Sunday night dinner:-)
review.reviewBody: Fabulous crew and staff (thank you Magda) :-) surprised about the quality of dinner too! Buffet but scrumptious (something for everyone . Chicken or steak or Mac n cheese etc )….  Wish they would have had more coffee available to go with the cheesecake dessert but no worries! Parking was a BREEZE!!! This is NOT located near downtown but on outskirts…. I envisioned pike place market … NOPE! Pulled in before boarding time and lot was empty.. made it great for my 81 yr old mother to walk to! Thanks!!! Went with my mother and nephew :-)

review.name: Run (don’t walk) away from this trip!
review.reviewBody: Friend and I booked the dinner cruise (Saturday night) a month in advance. We ended up on the Emerald Star. We pre-ordered four appetizers, one salmon and one pork chop. Extra drink tickets. Immediately after departure we were told that only the spinach dip was available and that we would be refunded for the other three apps. Refund TBD. (In reading other reviews, it appears this is common practice with this line with no refund being issued). Trying to get cocktail and soda refills was like pulling teeth! Two drinks all night. The salad was fine, the salmon was about the size of a cookie and tasted off. We didn’t finish it. The pork chop was floating in some kind of weird, watery gravy, and was beyond well done. We didn’t finish it. The dessert was some sort of gross canned peaches concoction, but because the whipped cream was warm to the touch and smelled sour we didn’t try it. One of the worst issues was how @&$!? hot it was in the cabin! Sweltering! All the windows were fogged up and ladies were using anything they could find to fan themselves. Bathrooms were dirty. Poorly understaffed with no service experience. The cruise itself was mediocre as far as sights and narration. And yes, I know that the point of the cruise isn’t the food. But for $400.00 plus tip, go have an epic dinner somewhere on the waterfront! Would NOT recommend.

review.name: Disappointed!
review.reviewBody:
We booked the August 27, 2023 Sunday Dinner Buffet/Tour as a private event for  39 people for our August celebrants. We had the upper deck for our group. As  the coordinator for this event, I could say I'm dissatisfied about the following:
1.  The temperature was uncomfortably 
      hot. The airconditioning system was 
      not sufficient to provide cool air on a
      hot Summer day. It was so hot inside!
      With this situation, the crew could
      have been proactive to offer cold 
      water with ice!  In fact, the only drink 
      that was free was water and it felt 
      warm because of the heat. Because 
      of the heat most  of our guests 
      stayed outside where it's cooler. So 
      whatever program prepared was 
      derailed. Very disappointing!
2.   The seating arrangement agreed 
       upon in advanced was not followed
       causing it to be overcrowded. 
       Seating layout for 39 people was 
       supplied by our group but the 
       tables and chairs were set up for 
       50. This was so inconsistent with how 
       the representative Cameron strictly 
       emphasized that a maximum of only 
       40 people will be allowed in the 
       upper deck. Clearly, this seems to 
       demonstrate the lack of 
       coordination and communication 
       within their company. 
 3.  The crew were generally nice but 
       seemed inexperienced in customer 
       service. For example, none of the 
       crew offered more water at any 
       table; guests were thirsty.
 4.   The tour route of the ship brought 
        us to unattractive industrial areas 
        showing old ugly ships and
        warehouses.  
        As the one coordinating for our 
       event, I recommended Waterways 
       because of a very positive 
       experience several years ago. The 
       tour passed the beautiful sceneries,
       like UW stadium and even Bill Gates
       waterfront house. This tour did not. 

For the price that we paid per person plus reservation fee, we expected better service,accommodation and tour. 
The food was great. Many loved the steak and Macaroni and Cheese. 

Overall, our group enjoyed the celebration as it was also their first time experience with dinner cruise buffet. Everyone was happy to meet coming from different States and foreign countries. 
However, I would not recommend this tour again.

review.name: Meh...Not Worth the Price
review.reviewBody:
Disappointing. We went on the Sunday Dinner Cruise, and was sub-par, to say the least. 

Seated next to the air conditioner, which was freezing cold, and quite noisy. Luckily, a couple offered to exchange tables with us. (Thank you again, if you're out there).
Ordered a Dungeness crab cake appetizer, and discovered that it was not available, even though I had been charged (No refund as of yet). 
The bathrooms are in need of repair. 
They ran out of desserts, so some attendees did not receive any. 

The cruise itself was lovely, and I'm not typically nit-picky, but for the price, I was expecting more. I wouldn't go again.

review.name: NO customer service and unannounced reduced cruise time
review.reviewBody: We signed up for the 2 hour Sunday dinner cruise, the cruise lasted 1.25 hours then returned to lake union dock area and floated for the last 45 min.  I know fuel is high right now but there was no notice about it and if we were going to float it would have been better in Lake Washington with a much better view than the navy ship area.  There was absolutely NO response to multiple calls and emails trying to change our reservation from 6 to 4 as 2 of our party came down with COVID and could not attend.  we left 3 voicemails and 3 emails and NEVER heard back from anyone.   We were extremely disappointed, especially because we had gone on the brunch cruise in 2020 during covid and had a nice experience.  At this point we won't book another cruise with Waterways!

review.name: Great Brunch and Water Cruise
review.reviewBody:
Sunday Brunch Cruise. Fabulous staff! Excellent food, cruise, narration of sites on the water.  Wonderful experience for my 92 year old Father. 
The entire staff took great care and effort to make this a special day. Thank you Pasqual and all who were involved to help.  Whether your visiting Seattle or live here, this is a must do adventure.

review.name: Love it!
review.reviewBody: So delicious yummy brunch! 😋 My family enjoyed our Valentines weekend brunch. It was a nice sunny day too in Seattle. What a memorable occasion :) Thank you Waterways Cruise! ❤️

review.name: Christmas Parade Dinner Cruise
review.reviewBody: We sat on the top floor of the yacht where there were only 12 people and the bottom is where larger parties and children sat; there may have been 30 down there.  Thus, it was not crowded on the cruise, which was nice.  Due to wind and slight rain on Dec. 23rd, it seemed as though we didn't cruise the whole scheduled route, but that's okay.  Just being with my husband on a dinner cruise was fabulous!

review.name: Dinner cruise
review.reviewBody: We enjoyed this, but the windows were fogged over and had condensation on the inside, and we couldn’t see anything. 😔 It was pretty disappointing. The food and atmosphere were otherwise enjoyable.

itemListElement.name: Seattle, WA to Victoria, BC High-Speed Passenger Ferry: ONE-WAY

name: Seattle, WA to Victoria, BC High-Speed Passenger Ferry: ONE-WAY
description: Skip the hassle of driving with FRS Clipper’s simple and easy downtown-to-downtown service! The Victoria Clipper V is a high-speed, passenger-only ferry and the fastest, most convenient way to travel between Seattle, WA and Victoria, BC. Sit back and relax, on your less than three-hour cruise through the Puget Sound to your destination.

review.name: Ferry to Victoria Cancelled
review.reviewBody: In January, we booked/paid for seats in April on the ferry from Seattle to Victoria to begin a 2 week vacation. Today, four days before our departure, we were informed by email that the ferry voyage has been canceled. Now I am scrambling to figure out how to get from Seattle to Victoria. Flights on airlines are running *three* times as much as our ferry tickets. This is a very expensive nightmare.

review.name: Great way to travel!
review.reviewBody: Booking online was easy, and the trip was comfortable. Ok food options on board. Staff is friendly.  We took a roundtrip from Seattle to Victoria to spend a few days on Vancouver island.  We were in economy, so didn't necessarily have the best views, but were able to go outside on the top deck to watch the Puget Sound sail by.  My kids loved it too.  We booked the area of economy with the tables, and the legroom was a little tight, but we got to sit together as a family, play cards, and eat.

review.name: Good Service
review.reviewBody: Efficient, good service. We were able to visit Victoria from Seattle on a ferry ride that took about 3 hours. We were able to include various sightseeing activities (food tour, Butchart Gardens) with our ferry ticket which was convenient, since it was our first time visiting Victoria.

review.name: Easy comfortable car-free transit to Victoria
review.reviewBody:
I live in Seattle and wanted a car-free trip to Victoria. From home, I took a bus and walked to Pier 69 where the FRS Clipper ships depart. Very early start to the day. It's an 8am departure but they ask people to arrive at 7AM. I wasn't quite that early, maybe 7:15AM. The check-in experience was easy. It felt like airline travel - assigned seats, different classes of seats, option to check bags, long wait between requested arrival time and departure time.

* On the boat, there are self-serve luggage racks in the center. Easy and free. I chose the econpan class seat so that I could have a window seat. Watching the scenery was entertaining and I had lots of space as solo traveler because no one was in the aisle seat.

* Nice benefit of paying for Clipper is leaving from downtown Seattle, cushy seats, and they manage the customs process. We were given paper forms and pencils so we could fill everything out before the boat docked. Because we went through customs as a group, it was quick with only the boat travelers in the lines.

review.name: Don't book the costly service, not worth it
review.reviewBody:
We booked in April for Aug 10th, the afternoon trip. One week before it got rescheduled to the morning ferry and reserved seats got changed and double booked. 
I wouldn't even let my dog go with this garbage service. Not worth the expensive comfort bookings at all.

review.name: Jipped out of my refund
review.reviewBody: I purchased 3 tickets to Victoria from Seattle. I read on the website that I can cancel up to 48 hours before departing. When I went to cancel, I was told that I misread the tickets. I can cancel if I purchased a specific ticket, huh? Okay, even though I paid for VIP top shelf tickets I still did not buy the right tickets? Wow. I had to immediately give them a date that I can travel again just to not lose the tickets. Lesson learned. Wait another thing they tell you is if you had just called us to book the tickets we would have explained this to you. I used their website, not a third party! Be aware...

review.name: CHAOS in Seattle, Improvement Needed
review.reviewBody: The boarding process was CHAOS in Seattle.  This company doesn't exhibit efficient efforts in handling large numbers of passengers.  We arrived 1.5 hours before our boarding time, had our coveted VERIFICATION card in hand then waited waited and waited without any further direction or instruction.  Well there might have been some but everytime FRS made a PA announcement there was a freight train rolling across the street so you can't understand whatever it was they were saying.  There are no signs to inform you what steps you need to take, such as having your passports verified and your boarding passes scanned.  Numerous people were arriving, milling around and did not know about this check-in process until several of us told them.  There is no que lines. signs or evidence of organization.  Finally a staff person came out and wandered around checking documents and handing out verification cards, tho at no time was she identified as an FRS employee, shirt, hat or even a name tag.  This was a sold-out boat so maybe they aren't used to such crowds, but still no que lines or directions, unless it was the useless PA system competing with the railroad.  Hey FRS send out an employee when a train is coming by and test your system to see if they can hear all the way to the end of the steps.  Finally, we board and the boat staff are competent and organized with a nice flat-water ride to Victoria.  When you arrive in Victoria you are split into two groups, one with luggage and one with walk off luggage only.  Both groups still wait onboard for at least 20 minutes while they crane over the luggage carts, probably for safety, but you must wait in your seat, no standing up until you are told you can stand up.  A crew member came out and started to vacuum the carpets around the empty seats while those of us with luggage in Group 2 waited for our turn to get off the ship.  Standing up to stretch, since I had been seated for most of the 3.5 hrs of the trip, I was promptly told I had to stay in my seat.  We were finally allowed to disembark and lo and behold, what do they have in Victoria, but que lines like at the airport.  Gosh they are so much smarter in Canada, I guess.  If your boat is full plan on it being another hour of line waiting from docking to clearing Customs.   By way of comparison, the MV Coho from Port Angeles came in after the FRS docked, unloaded passengers, vehicles, loaded vehicles and passengers for its return trip and left before I was done clearing Customs.  The unloading back in Seattle also has the wait in your seat until your group number is called BUT they queue you up on the outside deck to clear Customs so it is better than the loading CHAOS.  If you are going on the Clipper just know you will add at least 2 hours or more to your trip time and plan accordingly.  Travelled July 7 to the 11th 2024.

review.name: Great experience but wrong instructions
review.reviewBody:
The trip advisor instructions said to be at the pier at 8am. That's too late! You need to be on board 15 mins before departure time...this needs to be stressed in the directions.
Otherwise, excellent experience.

review.name: Great way to go to Victoria and back!
review.reviewBody: Everything ran smoothly for us! I had everything in order, my passport, confirmation printed. We showed up at about 7am, and there was a little line already. We waited; they checked our passport. I didn't have any luggage to check, just a carry on. We were in economy, which was fine. The seats were fine, we purchased a cheese and fruit plate (which they were out of on the way back). You can bring your own food and drinks (non-alcoholic) on board to consume as well. Got there on time. Everything went great on the way back as well. Kind of wish they had a return back to Seattle in the morning, but everything was great!

review.name: As advertised
review.reviewBody: Everything worked as advertised, including the discounted parking.  Embarkation and disembarkation went relatively quickly, although we had a sparse crowd on Tuesday.  We upgraded to sit upstairs and enjoyed the views and peace and quiet.  Tranquil waters this day.
